from henry henry spencer subject re life on mar in article schiewer don schiewer write what be the deal with life on mar i save the face and hear associate theory which sound thin to me the face be an accident of light and shadow there be many face in landform on earth none be artificial well exclude mount rushmore and the like there be also a smiley face on mar and a kermit the frog the question of life in a more mundane sense bacterium or the like be not quite close although the odd be against it and the most that the more orthodox exobiologist be hop for now be fossil there be currently no particular plan to do any further search for life are we go back to mar to look at thi face agian mar observer currently approach mar will probably try to get a better image or two of the face at some point it not high priority nobody take it very seriously the shadow half of the face do not look very face-like so all it will take be one shoot at a different sun angle to ruin the illusion all work be one man work henry spencer u of toronto zoology kipling henry utzoo henry 